Dialogs.Dialog: Rinko
Oh, by the way, did you see that thing the other day ▲主人公＊▲？
Huh？
When I say "that", I mean that: "Fluffy Stopover Town."
Is it a TV travel show？ No, I don't watch it.
Let's watch it！
I see, you haven't seen it...
Well then, do you know Enoshima？
Enoshima？ Well, sort of.
I heard it's a nice place, right？ It's not too close or too far, and you can go there in a day trip.
I see.
And you know, Enoshima has Shonan, right？ Shonan means youth, right？ It's like a gateway to youth, you know？
The gateway？ I don't know about that... In other words, do you want to go？
Oh, you mean Rinko？ Hmmm, I wonder - I thought you might want to go.
Me？ Well, I don't know...
Don't you wanna go there？ ...Hey？
Okay, so let's go, shall we？
Yay！ Then it's settled！ A samurai never says "no"！ You're a samurai today！ Hehe！
(You really wanted to go, ▲小早川＊▲...)
Well then, where are you ▲小早川＊▲...
Rinko
▲主人公＊▲.
▲小早川＊▲？
Hehe...
You're looking more stylish than usual, aren't you, ▲小早川＊▲...？
Because, you know... right？
Huh？
Well, it's all good！ Come on, let's go！ Youth awaits！
You're in a good mood. All right, let's go ▲小早川＊▲！
Rinko
▲主人公＊▲.
Ah, you're early, ▲小早川＊▲！
Hehe... it's because we're going to go to Enoshima, right？
Are you a little more stylish than usual, ▲小早川＊▲...？
Yeah, it's because it's Enoshima, right？
Okay, let's go！
Rinko
One question.
What？
You know, this train is an Enoden, right？ That means we're already in Shonan, right？
...I guess？ Why？
There's nothing but houses outside the window since a while ago... It doesn't look like Shonan, does it？
Didn't you see a glimpse of the ocean around Kugenuma just now？
Hmm...
No, let's go forward. Shonan is the place to be after getting on the Enoden. That's how it is.
What's with that... Oh well, I guess you're right？
That's right, Shonan is just a matter of how you feel. Let's go forward♪ Ah, since we're going to Shonan, I'm going to speak like this, okay？
Rinko
Heey, hey.
Hmm？
I knew it！ Riding the Enoden train is something to get excited about, isn't it？
It feels like a journey, after all.
Yeah. It does.
Hey, can I go to the front？
Yeah, it's fine, ah...
And she's gone...
Hah, we're here - this is Enoshima...
Rinko
You know... Just to be sure, I have a question. This is Enoshima, right？
I guess？ It says Enoshima Station.
What about the ocean？ Or rather, what about Enoshima？
I think I caught a glimpse of it from the Enoden earlier.
Enoshima is Enoshima, but it's not just another Enoshima, is it？
No way... Let's just head south for a bit, shall we？ Come on, let's go forward？
I don't need that kind of thing right now. Hah...
Hey.
Hah, we're here～.
Rinko
I'd say～！ I knew it, this is the Enoden Enoshima Station. It's so quaint！
I can't see the ocean or Enoshima, though.
You don't get it.
Thus, if you close your eyes and listen carefully, you will see the tidal waves...
I think I can hear it, or maybe not.
All right, I get it. Come on, let's go！
Rinko
Come on, over here！ Hurry up！
Hey, wait a minute！
Oh, Enoshima！
Here it is, Enoshima... A floating island！ The lighthouse, the shining sea！ It has to be like this！
Ah, now that's what I call Enoshima！
Yeah... Really nice view...
Who？ That's another Enoshima... Or so they said, and that's rude, isn't it？ It's rude to Enoshima-san.
Well, yeah. It was you who said that, you know, ▲小早川＊▲.
I see, hehe. Sorry, Enoshima-san. Let's go！
It's another beautiful day, you can see the island clearly.
Rinko
I'm home, Enoshima. I'm here again.
You must really like Enoshima.
Well, yeah. It's Rinko's territory now. Hah～, Green island！ Blue sea！ The long bridge！
...Benten Bridge it's quite long...
It's a bit of a walk across the street...
Rinko
Now then, it's a good day and it's almost time...
For what？
There you go again. You were really hoping for it.
Ah, perhaps！
That's right. Rinko's Lunch Box in Enoshima.
Yayー！ Then, are there many Enoshima specialties？
I don't know that many, so I'll cover them with this. Come on, find someplace with a good view！
Well then. First, let's see where we're going...
Should we go to ▲スポット名＊＊＊＊＊＊▲.
Rinko
Yeah. Maybe we should go there first. It's okay.
Thanks for the food！
Rinko
You're welcome... Isn't there a lot of Enoshima specialties on the island？ Handmade bento, you see, is a Rinko specialty.
Is that so？ Well, now that we've had lunch, the next step is...
Since we've come all this way, let's go to Samuel Cooking Garden. Come on, you want to go to the lighthouse, too, right？
Okay, let's go！
Well, I guess it's time to go over there...
Should we go next to ▲スポット名＊＊＊＊＊＊▲？
Rinko
Sure. Let's go！
I guess that's where we're going next...
Next, you wanna go to ▲スポット名＊＊＊＊＊＊▲？
Rinko
Let's go. Hehe, Rinko thought so too.
Rinko
Umm... I knew it！ The sea breeze is different. Shonan is the place to be！
I guess. Good thing we came, huh？
Yeah. Oh... look, a cat！ Hey, nyan cat♪
Oh, it's true.
Cat～ Cat～ Nyan♪
No response... What a pompous girl.
Hey, you're making me feel bad！ Ah...
And it's gone.
Yes. It's not like she's running away, it's like she can afford it... I wonder where she's going.
Hey, do you want to go along？
That sounds interesting！ ...But I will not. Not today.
Huh？
Come on, let's go！
Rinko
Hah, hah...
Hmm？ If you're tired, you want to take a break？
Not at all？ It's just, I'm taking a deep breath of sea breeze...
I see.
So that's Esker, huh... I think it's good.
...Want to take a break？
I'm fine―― Ah！ Look, there she is again！ The brown cat from before, she's looking at me. Hey.
And she's gone... She was not running away, she was just moping around. Maybe she's making fun of you and Rinko？
Maybe...
Rinko
Hah～...
Are you a little tired ▲小早川＊▲？
I'm fine.
I see.
What would you do if Rinko became the greatest person in Enoshima？
Greatest person？ ...What are you going to do？
Maintain Eskers on all hills.
(She must be tired.)
Oh, look！ There she is again！ The big brown tiger from earlier！
Where？
She' s already gone... she was looking this way again.
Maybe that girl is trying to tell you and Rinko to follow her？
Huh？？？
Rinko
Hmmm... I knew it, the wind is different. Shonan is different！
I see. Glad we came, huh？
Yeah. Thanks for bringing me.
You're welcome.
Did you know？ Somehow, you seem like a fresh Shonan Boy today, you know ▲主人公＊▲？
(I'm a little embarrassed.)
Rinko
Hmm！ That's good！ So many souvenir shops！
There are lots of tourists. It's like a tourist spot.
Seems like it. For normal Rinko this might be a little uncomfortable. But I'm really into it today.
Into it？ Why？
That is～... You see, today's Rinko is a Shonan girl, you know？ Oh, what a nice smell！
Grilled turban shells in a pot？ Want to try it？
The turban shell is a little splotchy on the tips... Oh, what's that？ There's some kind of retro bottle.
It's called "Shonan Cider."
I see！ Rinko will be over there then！
Rinko
The Naked Benten-sama, one of Japan's three great deities, is enshrined at this Hetsunomiya Shrine.
It is a god of marriage, but in the old days, it was said that if couples came together, Benten-sama would get jealous and make them break up, right？
I see, you know a lot about it？
Well, I guess？
Naked Benten-sama, huh...
Hmm？ Are you thinking about punishment？
No way！
Rinko
Hah... too much going down stairs, my knees are giggling...
Iwaya it's a little further.
That makes me hopeful...
Wow, it's so cool～！
There's a lot of staging and it's well maintained.
Yes. After all, here is the Celestial Maiden and the Five-headed Dragon...
Celestial Maiden？
...Eh？ What did Rinko say？ Come on, a little further in, let's go, okay？
Rinko
Lively, as always.
That's right. Besides, anytime you come in here, it smells delicious.
Grilled turban shells. Sure smells good, though.
Are you willing to take the plunge this time？
People, you know, they become adults when they taste turban shells.
Is that how it's done？
Rinko, you know, would like to stay a kid a little longer.
You won't eat it, you mean？
Rounded octopus crackers lined up.
Rinko
Hey, can you walk away for a minute？
Hmm？ ...Are you angry？
Not really... See, if you are too close, Benten-sama will punish us, right？
Do you mean jealousy？ It's a superstition. Besides, they say he's the god of marriage.
But, you know, just in case, okay？
Okay, so a little bit, huh, ▲小早川＊▲...？
Yeah. Just for a little while, okay？
Rinko
The Esker is... not really there. I see.
Give it up.
Looking at it this way, I guess the Dragon God here is the rascal.
The big one is the Dragon Palace, right？
Yep... But considering the glowing stones and the fact that it's deep in a cave, I knew this one was the last boss, right？
I guess. Hmm...
Well, I have a suggestion.
Hmm？
Maybe you and Rinko should read the guidebooks or something once in a while. We're not in elementary school...
Yes, I know.
Rinko
Hmmm... This whole area was Samuel's garden.
Yeah, it's a big place.
Oh, look, over there！ I see the lighthouse！
Okay, let's climb up.
Amazing！
Oh！
It is higher than it looks from the bottom, when you climb up.
It's built on the top of the island.
Yeah... I have a panoramic view of Shonan. Oh, I can see Eboshi-iwa.
It's often used in lyrics. Is that Kamakura over there？
Hah！ The wind is strong！ But it feels so good！ It give me a youthful feeling！
Yeah, I'm glad we came.
Let's go to the other side, shall we？ Come on, try to catch Rinko～！
Don't run, you're too young！
Rinko
Oh, look！ The Dragon Palace！
Yup. It's definitely a dragon...
It's a dragon... Enoshima island is a bit like an RPG. Celestial Maidens, dragons, and so on.
They're painted in a lot of different places.
Yeah. What if, in fact, it's all a flag and this is the cave of the last boss？
If this was the last boss, huh... Well, I guess I'll try to do the quest.
Then, chosen hero, slay the dragon！
Huh？ Me, a hero？
Yes. Princess Rinko will be waiting for you here. Do it and be done with it！
Chigogafuchi, huh... Looking at it this way, you can see that the seafloor has been raising up.
Rinko
Yeah... Iwaya over there is also called Ryugutsu, or Dragon Cave. I really feel like a dragon lives there.
I see.
By the way, wasn't there an Esker around here？
Esker is the escalator that connects those shrines, right？ I don't think so, do you？
Hah... I knew it.
Do you want to ride the Eskers that much？
I mean, I want to because I'm mad. I just remembered the stairs I just went down...
Indeed. That's why we'll climb up again...
Rinko
Hey, hey, cameraman-san. Is there a good vibe around here？
Yeah, I'll take a picture.
Hehe！
Rinko
Oh, this place is nice. It looks like Enoshima.
Okay, I'll take a picture.
Hehe！
Rinko
Hey, since we're at it, why don't you take a picture here, too？
Yes, let's do.
Huh, what's that？
Rinko
What, let Rinko see it too.
Wow... what does this mean？
I don't know, but with the position of the sun and the refraction of the lens, maybe it's a trick of light...
But, you see, it's kind of like...
Yup. It's like a Celestial Maiden's robe of feathers...
I'm sure that little brown tiger gave it to Rinko and you as a gift... Let's take good care of it.
Hmm？
Rinko
What, did you fail？
No, this may be...
Eh！ Could it be again？
Yay, a picture of a feather！
Yeah.
It's amazing... I wonder if coincidences like this are common...
Otherwise, you really are a Celestial Maiden, ▲小早川＊▲...
If so... would you be Rinko's dragon？
Of course.
Hehe, we'll always be together, won't we？
Well then... it's almost sunset.
Rinko
Hmmm... I must have passed by it somewhere...
What's wrong？
Actually, Rinko still wanted to go somewhere, but it's late, so better next time...
Oh, it's that little brown tiger... Wait a minute, I'm going to go say hello.
I lost her again... I'm pretty sure she's on this side of the road...
Our next destination is... the "Dragon Bell of Love".
"Dragon Bell of Love"... it's over there！
Rinko
Well... we've enjoyed Enoshima today, and the sun is about to set.
Hmm？
You know, at the end of the day, right？
Oh, I see. Okay, let's go！
The sunset is amazing... You wanted to come see it, ▲小早川＊▲？
Rinko
That's right. The legend of the Celestial Maiden and the Five-headed Dragon is written on the bell there.
"A Celestial Maiden and a Five-headed Dragon"？
It is said that a long time ago, a Five-headed Dragon who did nothing but evil fell in love with a Celestial Maiden on this island, then changed his mind and protected people.
So, in honor of the legend of the Maiden and the Dragon being united, the lovers who ring this bell are...
Said to be together forever.
So you wanted to come here, ▲小早川＊▲...？
Yeah. And you know...
Rinko
Doesn't that remind you？ Like in Atami...
"Aijo Cape"？
A little bit, right？
It's true.
Rinko
Doesn't that remind you？ You know, like in Rinko's rooftop...
When you confessed to me？
Rinko
I saw it on TV and Rinko remembered it too.
Still makes Rinko tear up sometimes just being with you like this.
I wanted to reiterate that here...
Why didn't you just say so from the beginning？
Because, you know, if I say something serious like that, I'm going to be laughed at.
I won't laugh... Thank you.
Yeah... You know what, maybe no one is looking at us right now...
I love you... Hehe... Shall we ring the bell？
All right.
It's something a little different from what I imagined！！
Sounds surprisingly sibilant, doesn't it？
But hey, sounds like a blessing, right？
Indeed.
The sunset is amazing. You wanted to come here, ▲小早川＊▲？
Rinko
Yeah. You know why？
That would be...
Then, here's a tip.
Rinko
There are a lot of locks around that bell... See, you saw that somewhere, right？
Ah... "Aijo Cape"？
Well said. Hehe, it's a bit like it, isn't it？
It's true.
Rinko
That day, we saw that beautiful sunset from the rooftop...
Certainly, the day you confessed to me――
Don't say it！ It's a bit embarrassing...
Rinko
It was on TV, and it made me remember. Once more...
Rinko is kinda shy, so I thought with the help of this place, I could say it right.
I always will love you, ▲主人公＊▲...
I feel the same for you, ▲小早川＊▲...
Shall we ring the bell？
That bell？
Yes. That bell says something about the legend of the Celestial Maiden and the Five-headed Dragon.
It is said that a long time ago, a Five-headed Dragon who did nothing but evil fell in love with a Celestial Maiden on this island, then changed his mind and protected people.
So, in honor of the legend of the Maiden and the Dragon being united, the lovers who ring this bell are...
Said they can be together forever.
So you wanted to come here, ▲小早川＊▲...？
Well, yeah. It's a little out of character for Rinko, so it's hard for me to say it.
I see. Okay, let's ring it up！
Ah！！ Isn't it a little Japanese？
That's a gratifying feeling...
Well, it's okay, isn't it？ These are memories only for you and Rinko, right？
I guess so.
Hey... it's just you and Rinko right now, right？
Yes.
Geez... Come on, over here. Why don't you come closer？
Hehe... It tasted like sea breeze.
It's because we're in Shonan.
The sunset is amazing... You wanted to come here ▲小早川＊▲？
Rinko
Yeah... I was thinking that I could use the power of that bell.
The power of the bell？
Long ago, a Five-headed Dragon who did nothing but evil fell in love with a Celestial Maiden on this island. To be loved by her, the dragon changed his ways and protected the people.
So, you know, the Maiden and the Dragon were united forever, so these bell- ringing lovers are...
Said to be together forever.
I see...
Besides, you know？ Doesn't that remind you of something？
Rinko
That bell is full of keys...
Ah... like "Aijo Cape" in Atami？
Hehe, I'm so glad you remembered.
Of course.
Rinko
Like Rinko, on that roof at the school building...
You mean when you confessed to me？
Rinko
Yeah... I saw it on TV and Rinko remembers it too. Hey, let's ring the bell, shall we？
Okay...
Ah！！ Huh？ It's somewhat different from what I imagined.
It looks like a temple...
Yup. But I think I might have found my courage.
Hey, Rinko, you know, sometimes I'm such a hassle because I don't have the courage to do this, but...
But I will always, always love you. I want to be with you...
Yeah, let's stay together.
Did Rinko's feelings get through to you？
I got them.
So, you know what I want to do next？
It's still a little embarrassing...
The sunset is nice here...
Rinko
Yeah. It's like the end of a day's adventure.
Adventure？
The Celestial Maiden and the Five-headed Dragon. It's written in English on the bell.
"The Celestial Maiden and the Five-headed Dragon". Sounds like an RPG, doesn't it？
Hey, hey, where's the ending？
Ending？ I don't know what you wanna do.
Well... First, the Dragon and the Princess ring the bell.
Am I the Dragon？
Would you have preferred the Princess？
I'll take the Dragon.
Ah！！ I knew it, this sound is so Japanese.
The Maiden and Dragon fit better, don't they？
Okay, then the rest of the story. Then Dragon...
He gently kissed the Maiden.
Hey, the train is coming, ▲小早川＊▲！
Rinko
Sorry, my bad！ Sorry for keeping you wait.
Did you buy something？
Sort of. See.
Ah, the Dragon strap！
Yes... How do you like it？ This Dragon is rather handsome, isn't he？
Really？ I'm sure there's something cooler, right？
Hmm, I think there might be... Well, it's okay. Rinko likes this！ Hehe！
I see. Then, should I buy a similar one？
You know... What are you going to do if you buy a dragon？ If you're going to buy a dragon, you're going to be the world's prettiest Maiden, right？
Oh, here comes the train！ Hurry！
(Sounds like you made great memories today. I'm glad, ▲小早川＊▲...)
Rinko
It's kind of mysterious.
Mysterious？
This station, you know, in the evening, feels more like a station in our own town than a travel destination...
Yup. I think I know what you mean...
It's as if, you know, they're telling me to come again.
When we come to Enoshima, you become a Maiden, ▲小早川＊▲.
What？ I've always been a maiden！
Ouch...
Train's coming！ Hurry！
(It's hard to understand the heart of a maiden...)
